label.value: Stage I Colon Neuroendocrine Tumor AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I includes: T1, N0, M0. T1: Tumor invading the lamina propria or submucosa and measuring 2 cm or less. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIA Colon Neuroendocrine Tumor AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIA includes: T2, N0, M0. T2: Tumor invading the muscularis propria or measuring more than 2 cm with invasion of the lamina propria or submucosa. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIB Colon Neuroendocrine Tumor AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIB includes: T3, N0, M0. T3: Tumor invading through the muscularis propria into subserosal tissue without penetration of overlying serosa. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Junctional Escape Rhythm by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a junctional rhythm that arises as a physiologic response to extreme slowing or arrest of sinus node activity. In this setting, a faster junctional rhythm may be a normal response to a very slow or absent sinus rate. (CDISC)

label.value: Nonconducted P Wave Physiology Not Defined by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a P wave that either does not conduct to the ventricle or that does not result in ventricular activation.

label.value: Supraventricular Escape Beat by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a compensatory supraventricular complex that occurs following a prolonged RR interval. (CDISC)
